arch:property.oc:show_val: North end W CP East, area of robbed pavers (Tr. 97, 2004, Locus 23).

A fill locus containing a combination of course and fine soils, including silt, sand, granules and pebbles, with a Munsell Color 7.5 YR 4/6 (Strong Brown). The fill was compacted, and served as leveling between the Locus 9 terracing course and the Locus 7 leveling course. The locus contained some pottery and bone.
Soil fill locus between Loci 7 and 9
1.6 m north south-by-2.0 m east west.
Phase V: Late Nabataean CE 1st c. redesign and repairs.
